lead_paragraph: Jabari Parker made a driving basket with 10.1 seconds left to put Milwaukee ahead and Tyler Ennis hit two free throws that sealed the Bucks' 113-110 win over the Orlando Magic on Friday night.

headline.print_headline: Parker's Driving Layup Carries Bucks Past Magic 113-110
